The diary has a **maximum capacity of 10,000** remember?

```python
class ReplayBuffer:
    def __init__(self, capacity=10000):
```

So:
- Agent makes 74,800 decisions total ✅
- Writes all of them in diary ✅
- But diary only keeps the **latest 10,000** ✅
- Oldest entries get deleted automatically when full

---

**Simple analogy:**

Diary has only 10,000 pages 📔

After page 10,000 is full — when agent writes page 10,001, the oldest page 1 gets torn out automatically.

So the diary always has the **most recent 10,000 experiences** — not all 74,800.

---

This is actually intentional — old early experiences where agent was playing randomly are less useful than recent experiences where agent is smarter. 😄

